sunny and calm- water very murky with algae scum near shore- clearer out in the lake.

Algae overload.  Especially bad near shore around most of the lake but especially at north and south ends.  Wouldn't let my dogs near it.

Algae last few days near shore has been terrible.  Not fit for humans or animals to be in.  Suspended algae in center of lake beginning to clear although I still wouldn't swim in it.  Water quality improved somewhat today (9/17) and much of the floating algae mats with 40 - 50 feet of shore have suddenly disappeared.

Partly to mostly cloudy.  Algae slicks beginning to form at south end of lake.  Water quality deteriorating.
